column1: If you have NOT placed this widget in the Group Profile Placement area and you "lock" it, then this widget will NOT be available to Group Owners for placing on the Group. If you have placed this widget in the Group Profile Placement area and you "lock" it, then Group Owners will NOT be able to remove it or drag-n-drop it.
column2: If you have NOT placed this widget in the Group Profile Placement area and you "lock" it, then this widget will NOT be available to Group Owners for placing on the Group. If you have placed this widget in the Group Profile Placement area and you "lock" it, then Group Owners will NOT be able to remove it or drag-n-drop it.

From the Global Settings of this plugin, you have allowed Group Owners to be able to arrange, add and remove widgets from the profile of their Groups. However, you still have control over what Group Profile widgets should be available to Group Owners, which widgets they should NOT be able to remove, and which ones they should be able to remove. If you have added a new plugin on your site, and would like its widget to be shown on Group Profiles and NOT be removable by Group Owners, then you can drop that widget into Group Profile below. If you would like to show an announcement, or any HTML content on Group Profiles, and NOT allow Group Owners to be able to remove it, then you can do that as well below. If there is a widget coming on profiles of Groups of your site that you want to be removed, then you can do that below; and many more such actions. If you drop a widget from a different plugin into the Group Profile, then Group Owners will NOT be able to remove it or drag-n-drop it. If you "lock" a Group Profile widget that has NOT been placed in the Group Profile Placement area, then that widget will NOT be available to Group Owners for placing on the Group. If you "lock" a Group Profile widget that has been placed in the Group Profile Placement area, then Group Owners will NOT be able to remove it or drag-n-drop it.
NOTE: If you have placed "Ad Campaign" or "Html Block" on this group, then once you click on the "Save Changes" link, you will neither be able to change the position nor edit that block. So, if you want to do so, you will have to remove that block from the Group and save changes and then place it again from the Available Blocks.
